contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:10.285 --> 02:15.285
Subtitles by explosiveskull

02:16.276 --> 02:19.611
107, 108, 109, 110.

02:19.613 --> 02:21.313
That's the last one.

02:21.315 --> 02:24.283
Uh, it's like a hundred a gram
is what, 41k?

02:24.285 --> 02:26.318
Are we seriously doing
500 per vial?

02:26.320 --> 02:27.552
I think that's kind of cheap.

02:27.554 --> 02:30.389
Uh-uh. 500 in Brooklyn,
750 in the city.

02:30.391 --> 02:31.522
That's what Coco said.

02:31.524 --> 02:35.326
22 plus 44 plus 20 equals...

02:35.328 --> 02:36.695
Is...

02:36.697 --> 02:38.330
83.

02:38.332 --> 02:41.399
Okay, we got 83k right here.

02:41.401 --> 02:45.036
My dad's definitely gonna wonder
how I paid off my student loans.

02:45.038 --> 02:46.904
$83,000.

02:46.906 --> 02:48.907
Maybe I'll just do it slowly,
like once a week.

02:48.909 --> 02:52.044
Is it bad that I don't feel bad
about this, like, at all?

02:52.046 --> 02:54.845
I felt way worse
when I was waiting tables.

02:54.847 --> 02:58.582
- [DISTANT SIRENS]
- Remember this moment.

02:58.584 --> 03:01.886
Everything's about to change.

03:01.888 --> 03:03.855
[SIRENS APPROACH]

03:03.857 --> 03:06.558
- [BANGING]
- MAN: Open up!

03:06.560 --> 03:09.361
Police! You've got two seconds
to open this door!

03:09.363 --> 03:10.698
- Just leave it.
- Go, go, go.

03:12.532 --> 03:13.834
Open up!

03:15.803 --> 03:19.474
[SIRENS WAILING]

03:30.049 --> 03:31.582
Do you wanna get caught,
is that what you want?

03:31.584 --> 03:32.950
What the fuck is wrong with you?

03:32.952 --> 03:34.885
Coco's gonna slit
our fucking throats!

03:34.887 --> 03:37.588
- Trying to bounce, bitch?
- Whoa, put that thing down.

03:37.590 --> 03:39.393
You scared the shit out of me!

03:40.960 --> 03:43.128
Excuse me, ma'am,
my friend is sitting here.

03:43.130 --> 03:46.897
- Oh, of course, I'm sorry.
- Sorry.

03:46.899 --> 03:49.901
Here, I'll help you up.
Sorry.

03:49.903 --> 03:51.069
- [SLAP]
- Oh! It's okay.

03:51.071 --> 03:52.570
I'm sorry.

03:52.572 --> 03:55.140
Thank you very much.
I'm so sorry.

03:55.142 --> 03:56.808
Do you have everything?
I think so.

03:56.810 --> 03:58.546
- Okay.
- Thanks.

04:23.771 --> 04:26.738
[PHONE VIBRATES]
Shit.

04:26.740 --> 04:29.707
They took the stuff, all of it.

04:29.709 --> 04:31.943
It's a fucking miracle
we got away.

04:31.945 --> 04:34.645
- [KNOCKS]
- Last night?

04:34.647 --> 04:35.981
About 80 worth.

04:35.983 --> 04:38.784
No, no, no, nobody saw us.

04:38.786 --> 04:40.551
No, we were just unpacking
and weighing it.

04:40.553 --> 04:42.053
I swear, we had no time
to sell any of it.

04:42.055 --> 04:44.392
- [KNOCKING]
- Somebody's in here!

04:45.526 --> 04:46.825
What?

04:46.827 --> 04:48.863
Good morning.
Tickets, please.

04:51.164 --> 04:53.031
Uh...

04:53.033 --> 04:55.032
You look very familiar.

04:55.034 --> 04:57.969
I'm a model and an actress, so
you've probably seen my face...

04:57.971 --> 05:00.137
No, I, uh...

05:00.139 --> 05:03.140
I don't watch TV.
My bad.

05:03.142 --> 05:05.078
May I have your ticket, please?

05:13.152 --> 05:15.152
Okay, you can stop pretending
like you don't know me now.

05:15.154 --> 05:16.955
Goddess Vesper.

05:16.957 --> 05:19.123
Listen, my friend and I
don't have tickets.

05:19.125 --> 05:21.625
- Your friend?
- She's sitting at the back.

05:21.627 --> 05:24.061
- What's your destination?
- Montpellier.

05:24.063 --> 05:26.733
Uh, that's about $80
times two.

05:28.702 --> 05:30.702
- 10 minutes.
- 30.

05:30.704 --> 05:32.036
- 15.
- 20.

05:32.038 --> 05:34.940
And I'll pretend
you're not high.

05:34.942 --> 05:36.177
All right, let's do this.

06:04.805 --> 06:07.074
What the fuck
you looking at?

06:13.779 --> 06:15.012
Lick it.

06:15.014 --> 06:17.815
Thank you, Goddess.

06:17.817 --> 06:19.519
Thank you.

06:33.733 --> 06:36.000
[WHISTLES]

06:36.002 --> 06:37.671
[CONTINUES WHISTLING]

06:41.974 --> 06:42.909
[WHISTLING]

06:46.747 --> 06:49.584
[WHISTLING
"ROW, ROW, ROW YOUR BOAT"]

07:08.334 --> 07:11.671
<i>♪♪</i>

07:22.214 --> 07:23.748
Watch where you're going.

07:23.750 --> 07:25.685
You watch where
I'm going, asshole.

08:02.089 --> 08:04.222
Hey, are you sure
she's gonna be there long?

08:04.224 --> 08:07.157
- Possibly.
- What if she got a caretaker?

08:07.159 --> 08:09.394
[MAN LAUGHING]

08:09.396 --> 08:14.168
You always come back,
you old witch.

08:22.274 --> 08:24.077
[LAUGHS]

08:25.745 --> 08:28.113
- Coco called.
- Shit. What did he say?

08:28.115 --> 08:32.183
We have to be back here
in two days, noon or sooner.

08:32.184 --> 08:35.222
We've got 48 hours,
starting now.

08:39.424 --> 08:40.961
[ENGINE STARTS]

08:55.075 --> 08:57.976
TILDA: <i>So how do you
wanna do this?</i>

08:57.978 --> 09:00.211
PETULA: <i>Well, you know Daphne.</i>

09:00.213 --> 09:02.817
<i>She's not just gonna
let us in like that.</i>

09:04.950 --> 09:08.656
<i>We'll need to search the
whole house to find the safe.</i>

09:09.989 --> 09:11.456
<i>To do so,</i>

09:11.458 --> 09:14.092
<i>we're gonna
have to play the game.</i>

09:14.094 --> 09:16.126
[LAUGHTER]

09:16.128 --> 09:18.395
GIRL: We're doing the game
we do every day. "Hospital."

09:18.397 --> 09:20.865
- We have to play.
- That's boring.

09:20.867 --> 09:22.067
We have to play.

09:22.069 --> 09:25.069
That's annoying.
I hate it.

09:25.071 --> 09:26.837
I'm Dr. Petula.

09:26.839 --> 09:28.807
Welcome to my doll's hospital.

09:28.809 --> 09:31.175
Well, Doctor,
this is my daughter Tilda,

09:31.177 --> 09:32.910
and she isn't feeling well.

09:32.912 --> 09:34.813
No wonder. We're playing
your stupid game.

09:34.815 --> 09:36.280
Lay down, daughter.

09:36.282 --> 09:38.783
I'm not gonna let you two
tell me what to do

09:38.785 --> 09:40.117
because you're not my mom!

09:40.119 --> 09:42.120
- Yes, I am your mom.
- You're not!

09:42.122 --> 09:43.288
- Yes, I am!
- Stop it!

09:43.290 --> 09:44.823
[SCREAMS]

09:44.825 --> 09:46.857
PETULA: <i>Once we get
into the house,</i>

09:46.859 --> 09:49.226
<i>whatever she asks you to do,
you're gonna have to do it.</i>

09:49.228 --> 09:51.098
<i>No excuses.</i>

09:52.965 --> 09:56.336
<i>She says, we obey.
Is that clear?</i>

10:00.140 --> 10:02.175
<i>Tilda, is that clear?</i>

10:31.103 --> 10:35.240
[HUMMING]

10:35.242 --> 10:40.448
[HUMMING CONTINUES]

10:49.289 --> 10:54.462
[TILDA WHISTLES
"ROW, ROW, ROW YOUR BOAT"]

10:56.296 --> 10:57.765
Hey, Mom.

11:03.570 --> 11:05.205
You okay, Mom?

11:08.575 --> 11:12.146
Hey, darling.
How was school?

11:13.445 --> 11:15.346
It was good.

11:15.348 --> 11:17.284
They let us out early.

11:19.853 --> 11:21.287
I'm hungry.

11:23.422 --> 11:26.124
Of course.
Of course you are!

11:26.126 --> 11:28.963
I was just about
to start cooking.

11:32.531 --> 11:33.865
[CLATTERING]

11:33.867 --> 11:38.303
[WRAPPER CRINKLING]

11:38.305 --> 11:41.573
[OPENING JAR]

11:41.575 --> 11:43.109
[UTENSILS CLATTERING]

11:55.888 --> 11:57.323
PETULA: <i>Remember the rules.</i>

11:58.992 --> 12:00.891
<i>Rule number one:</i>

12:00.893 --> 12:03.096
<i>Everyone must play.</i>

12:05.866 --> 12:07.932
<i>Rule number two:</i>

12:07.934 --> 12:10.070
<i>No outsiders allowed.</i>

12:14.140 --> 12:16.173
<i>Rule number three:</i>

12:16.175 --> 12:17.844
<i>Nobody leaves.</i>

12:58.550 --> 13:01.619
Come here! Your nails!
They're too long and dirty!

13:01.621 --> 13:03.288
I wasn't done.

13:03.290 --> 13:05.590
Go wash them.
Immediately.

13:05.592 --> 13:08.195
And brush your teeth too!

13:10.397 --> 13:12.199
He'll be here any minute.

13:21.206 --> 13:23.341
What are you still doing here?

13:23.343 --> 13:25.643
Because my nails aren't dirty.

13:25.645 --> 13:27.444
I'll do it myself.
Come here!

13:27.446 --> 13:29.579
Mom?

13:29.581 --> 13:32.318
- Mom!
- [DOORBELL RINGS]

13:34.487 --> 13:37.257
[DOORBELL RINGING]

13:39.693 --> 13:42.492
[HINGE SQUEAKS]

13:42.494 --> 13:44.062
Help me.

13:44.064 --> 13:45.432
PETULA: Get in.

13:49.234 --> 13:50.367
TILDA: Come on.

13:50.369 --> 13:52.605
Mom, the doctor's here!

13:57.076 --> 13:58.511
PETULA:
How are you doing, ma'am?

13:59.579 --> 14:01.348
Welcome back, Doctor.

14:21.200 --> 14:23.067
PETULA: Inhale for me.

14:23.069 --> 14:24.604
Exhale.

14:25.772 --> 14:27.404
Everything looks fine here.

14:27.406 --> 14:30.308
How strange.
She's been coughing all week.

14:30.310 --> 14:33.343
[COUGHING]

14:33.345 --> 14:36.246
I'll prescribe something
for that.

14:36.248 --> 14:39.149
And her posture
is terrible too.

14:39.151 --> 14:42.153
Her balance is very bad
as well.

14:42.155 --> 14:45.559
All right, let's see
what's going on here.

14:53.565 --> 14:55.002
Don't be scared.

15:01.340 --> 15:03.774
Rule number one.

15:03.776 --> 15:05.713
Everyone must play.

15:09.349 --> 15:10.751
[PETULA SIGHS]

15:13.386 --> 15:14.355
Mm.

15:17.357 --> 15:18.392
[WHISPERS]
Sorry.

15:22.429 --> 15:24.529
[SCREAMING]

15:24.531 --> 15:26.597
- Perfectly healthy.
- Oh!

15:26.599 --> 15:28.332
Thank goodness!

15:28.334 --> 15:31.669
Oh, darling, what do we say
to the doctor, hmm?

15:31.671 --> 15:34.404
"Thank you, Doctor."

15:34.406 --> 15:36.841
All done. She's shy.

15:36.843 --> 15:39.709
Doctor, can I get you something
to drink or a snack perhaps?

15:39.711 --> 15:41.779
I made some ice-cold lemonade...

15:41.781 --> 15:44.050
You forgot to measure me.

15:46.286 --> 15:49.790
I was just about
to measure you.

15:54.828 --> 15:56.726
Where are you, tape?

15:56.728 --> 15:58.829
Tape.

15:58.831 --> 16:00.564
Did you forget it, Doctor?

16:00.566 --> 16:02.469
No, I'm positive
I put it in here.

16:07.773 --> 16:10.308
Rule number three:

16:10.310 --> 16:11.645
Nobody leaves.

16:23.623 --> 16:25.758
[DAPHNE HUMMING]

16:39.171 --> 16:42.675
[HUMMING CONTINUES]

17:03.796 --> 17:04.861
[CLEARS THROAT]

17:04.863 --> 17:06.496
Shh.

17:06.498 --> 17:08.832
DAPHNE: Doctor,
is everything okay?

17:08.834 --> 17:10.570
Yes, ma'am, all's good.

17:16.642 --> 17:18.208
Doctor?

17:18.210 --> 17:20.413
Could you please pass the salt?

17:35.929 --> 17:38.595
We have 41 hours left.
There's not much time.

17:38.597 --> 17:40.598
Doctor...

17:40.600 --> 17:42.836
you must be exhausted.

17:44.403 --> 17:46.906
Why don't I show you
to your room?

18:18.705 --> 18:20.274
[HINGE SQUEAKS]

18:32.684 --> 18:35.686
Well, sleep well, Doctor.

18:35.688 --> 18:37.357
Thank you, ma'am.

18:40.927 --> 18:43.330
It's good to have you back.

18:51.770 --> 18:52.772
[SIGHS]

19:41.653 --> 19:45.291
[WATER RUNNING]

20:14.720 --> 20:15.888
PETULA: Tilda?

20:36.843 --> 20:38.010
[SIGHS]

20:46.753 --> 20:48.622
- [GASPS]
- Hello, Doctor.

20:51.690 --> 20:55.027
PETULA: I just came down
to get a glass to water.

20:56.828 --> 20:58.097
But of course.

21:06.805 --> 21:08.542
I can't sleep.

21:12.745 --> 21:15.681
- I better get back to bed.
- Please stay.

21:18.049 --> 21:20.353
I feel safe around you.

21:51.217 --> 21:55.155
[MOANING]

22:03.662 --> 22:07.099
[DISTANT MOANING]

22:20.179 --> 22:22.213
Are you trying to bounce, bitch?

22:22.215 --> 22:23.880
What the fuck is wrong with you?
You scared me!

22:23.882 --> 22:25.783
Holy shit.
Put that thing down.

22:25.785 --> 22:28.486
And don't fuck with the mailbox
until we're done, okay?

22:28.488 --> 22:29.820
Okay, I was just
checking my phone.

22:29.822 --> 22:31.221
Geez, are you fucking serious?

22:31.223 --> 22:32.790
You wanna get caught?
Is that what you want?

22:32.792 --> 22:35.059
No, Petula.
I don't wanna get caught.

22:35.061 --> 22:37.761
I just wanna get this over with
fucking ASAP, okay?

22:37.763 --> 22:39.796
What if she put everything
in a bank account?

22:39.798 --> 22:41.265
What if she didn't?

22:41.267 --> 22:43.633
Well, how much did she
give you for the physical?

22:43.635 --> 22:45.571
I don't know.
I didn't look yet.

22:47.139 --> 22:48.141
Shit.

22:50.709 --> 22:52.543
Are you fucking kidding me?

22:52.545 --> 22:54.745
Are you fucking kidding me?
Is she fucking...

22:54.747 --> 22:56.112
- What is wrong with her?
- It's all right. Just relax.

22:56.114 --> 22:57.814
Coco's gonna slit
our fucking throats!

22:57.816 --> 23:00.650
We have 28 hours left.
Plenty of time to find the safe.

23:00.652 --> 23:02.119
Then let's get cracking,
and let's do it now, okay?

23:02.121 --> 23:04.220
God, you have no idea
what fucking crazy cuckoo

23:04.222 --> 23:05.989
Daphne made me do last night.

23:05.991 --> 23:08.258
What?

23:08.260 --> 23:10.593
She made me, like...

23:10.595 --> 23:12.295
fuck her.

23:12.297 --> 23:14.063
- What?
- God.

23:14.065 --> 23:17.200
Really don't make me
say it again.

23:17.202 --> 23:20.303
I fucking heard you.
I fucking heard you!

23:20.305 --> 23:22.105
- Shh!
- Oh, my God.

23:22.107 --> 23:25.141
Did she make you come?
Did she pay you?

23:25.143 --> 23:26.877
[GIGGLING]

23:26.879 --> 23:30.684
Oh, my God. Poor Daphne.
She's fucking obsessed, man.

23:32.817 --> 23:36.555
<i>♪♪ [SERENE]</i>

23:44.063 --> 23:46.897
[BIRD SQUAWKING]

23:46.899 --> 23:48.668
[TILDA SQUAWKS, LAUGHS]

23:49.901 --> 23:51.802
Aw, are you okay, girl?

23:51.804 --> 23:54.572
Yeah. Yeah, I'm perfect.

23:54.574 --> 23:55.672
[CHUCKLES]

23:55.674 --> 23:58.141
Can I have some yum yum,
please?

23:58.143 --> 24:00.244
Uh, I think you've had enough.

24:00.246 --> 24:02.211
I thought we were
splitting it 50/50?

24:02.213 --> 24:04.715
Yeah, we are, but I'm not
gonna share my half with you,

24:04.717 --> 24:06.249
if you're gonna binge on it now,
Snow White.

24:06.251 --> 24:07.953
Just give it to me.

24:09.788 --> 24:10.987
Okay.

24:10.989 --> 24:12.989
- Geez, have it.
- Thank you.

24:12.991 --> 24:15.092
The fucking big deal is.

24:15.094 --> 24:17.162
Just some Vicodin.

24:18.331 --> 24:20.300
Tilda, this is not Vicodin.

24:21.933 --> 24:22.967
What?

24:22.969 --> 24:24.200
How much have you been taking?

24:24.202 --> 24:26.637
What did you give me?

24:26.639 --> 24:29.809
<i>♪♪ [ETHEREAL]</i>

24:31.177 --> 24:33.177
[GIGGLING]

24:33.179 --> 24:35.778
WOMAN: Tilda, Tilda.

24:35.780 --> 24:37.313
Tilda.

24:37.315 --> 24:39.283
Tilda!

24:39.285 --> 24:41.819
Let's go to the tree house.

24:41.821 --> 24:42.986
Tilda, Tilda.

24:42.988 --> 24:44.721
Hey, look at me.

24:44.723 --> 24:47.256
You're really high right now.

24:47.258 --> 24:50.828
You've taken a lot of PCP,
like a lot.

24:50.830 --> 24:52.396
You have no fucking idea.

24:52.398 --> 24:55.165
Okay, make room, Tills,
I'm coming in.

24:55.167 --> 24:59.003
[SPEAKS IN REVERSE]

24:59.005 --> 25:01.304
I'm just gonna be right back,
okay, Tilda?

25:01.306 --> 25:03.674
Just stay right there.
[ECHOING]

25:03.676 --> 25:05.712
[CHUCKLING]

25:09.748 --> 25:12.285
[GIRLS GIGGLING]

25:55.294 --> 25:56.893
YOUNG PETULA: We're doing
the game we do every day.

25:56.895 --> 25:59.295
- We have to play.
- That's boring.

25:59.297 --> 26:01.031
We have to play.

26:01.033 --> 26:02.832
I don't care.

26:02.834 --> 26:05.334
I'm Dr. Petula.
Welcome to my doll's hospital.

26:05.336 --> 26:08.471
Well, this is my daughter Tilda.
She isn't feeling well.

26:08.473 --> 26:10.807
No wonder.
You're playing this stupid game.

26:10.809 --> 26:12.976
I'm not gonna let you two
boss me around

26:12.978 --> 26:16.345
to play this stupid game
because you're not my mom!

26:16.347 --> 26:17.747
- Yes, I am!
- You're not!

26:17.749 --> 26:20.817
- Yes, I am!
- Stop it, stop it!

26:20.819 --> 26:22.052
[DAPHNE SCREAMS]

26:22.054 --> 26:23.954
[THUD]

26:23.956 --> 26:28.361
<i>♪♪ [OMINOUS]</i>

26:43.942 --> 26:46.275
YOUNG PETULA: It's not
our fault. Remember that.

26:46.277 --> 26:47.780
YOUNG TILDA: I know.

26:49.180 --> 26:52.248
YOUNG PETULA: But if we
do get caught lying,

26:52.250 --> 26:55.218
we'll never get to
see Daphne again.

26:55.220 --> 26:57.323
YOUNG TILDA: I know, I know.

27:15.975 --> 27:17.474
Hi.

27:17.476 --> 27:19.942
- Hi.
- Hi.

27:19.944 --> 27:22.345
I'm Detective Siegel.

27:22.347 --> 27:24.450
I came to find out
what happened.

27:29.354 --> 27:32.890
We were playing
in the tree house,

27:32.892 --> 27:37.897
and Daphne just fell out.

27:43.235 --> 27:47.373
How exactly did she
just fall out?

27:51.576 --> 27:52.978
Um...

28:12.832 --> 28:14.163
- DOCTOR: Mrs. Peters?
- Yes.

28:14.165 --> 28:15.498
Your granddaughter's
doing fine.

28:15.500 --> 28:17.333
- She just woke up.
- Ohh!

28:17.335 --> 28:21.971
But her lower abdomen
has been critically damaged.

28:21.973 --> 28:24.373
Unfortunately, I doubt
she'll ever be able to conceive.

28:24.375 --> 28:25.844
Oh, my God.

28:28.346 --> 28:33.552
<i>♪♪ [DARK]</i>

29:09.287 --> 29:12.525
<i>♪♪ [TENSE]</i>

29:25.103 --> 29:26.402
[PETULA SCREAMS]

29:26.404 --> 29:27.507
No!
[SCREAMS]

29:34.546 --> 29:39.682
[TRAIN HORN BLARING]

29:39.684 --> 29:43.956
[TICKING]

29:49.594 --> 29:51.594
PETULA: Tilda!

29:51.596 --> 29:53.663
Tilda!

29:53.665 --> 29:55.631
We gotta go!
We gotta go now!

29:55.633 --> 29:57.569
Come on, we gotta go now!

30:01.306 --> 30:02.909
Shit.

30:05.643 --> 30:07.913
Can we just get our phones,
please?

30:14.620 --> 30:20.590
<i>♪ Oh, yes,
I'm the great pretender ♪</i>

30:20.592 --> 30:26.429
<i>♪ Pretending
that I'm doing well ♪</i>

30:26.431 --> 30:32.201
<i>♪ My need is such
I pretend too much ♪</i>

30:32.203 --> 30:37.541
<i>♪ I'm lonely,
but no one can tell ♪</i>

30:37.543 --> 30:43.513
<i>♪ Oh, yes,
I'm the great pretender ♪</i>

30:43.515 --> 30:49.352
<i>♪ Adrift in a world of my own ♪</i>

30:49.354 --> 30:55.124
<i>♪ I play the game,
but to my real shame ♪</i>

30:55.126 --> 30:59.565
<i>♪ You've left me
to dream all alone ♪</i>

31:30.129 --> 31:32.661
MAN: <i>Siegel,
where the hell are you?</i>

31:32.663 --> 31:36.568
<i>[DISTORTED RADIO CHATTER]</i>

31:43.342 --> 31:45.708
[PHONE RINGS]

31:45.710 --> 31:47.646
Montpellier Police Station,
Detective Siegel.

31:54.719 --> 31:56.055
Yes, ma'am.

31:57.422 --> 31:59.288
I'll take care of her
personally.

31:59.290 --> 32:00.823
DAPHNE: My dolls.

32:00.825 --> 32:03.259
- [GASPING]
- Shh, my darlings.

32:03.261 --> 32:05.328
It's okay.

32:05.330 --> 32:07.333
Mother is here.

32:11.170 --> 32:13.637
Mother has always been here,

32:13.639 --> 32:17.306
but now you're back
where you belong.

32:17.308 --> 32:18.574
[GROANING]

32:18.576 --> 32:20.342
Oh, shh, shh, shh.

32:20.344 --> 32:22.512
All is well, my darlings.

32:22.514 --> 32:24.313
[GROANING CONTINUES]

32:24.315 --> 32:26.184
My dolls...
Hey, stop it!

32:28.353 --> 32:31.287
My silly girls.
[GIGGLES]

32:31.289 --> 32:34.357
You were never fit
for the outside world.

32:34.359 --> 32:36.426
In this house,
nothing has changed.

32:36.428 --> 32:37.494
Shh.

32:37.496 --> 32:40.263
I've never changed.

32:40.265 --> 32:44.234
Here, everything is possible!

32:44.236 --> 32:48.104
You know, a mother must always
forgive her children.

32:48.106 --> 32:49.840
We are a family.

32:49.842 --> 32:52.609
- [PETULA GRUNTS]
- Shh!

32:52.611 --> 32:54.814
Quiet now, quiet.

32:56.614 --> 32:58.747
Reality will never
keep up with our dreams.

32:58.749 --> 33:02.218
- [GIGGLES]
- [DOORBELL RINGS]

33:02.220 --> 33:04.420
- Girls?
- [SOBS]

33:04.422 --> 33:06.523
You stay put now.

33:06.525 --> 33:08.661
Mother will be right back.

33:21.840 --> 33:24.874
[PETULA GRUNTS]

33:24.876 --> 33:29.414
[WATER DRIPPING]

33:37.523 --> 33:39.156
Detective.

33:39.158 --> 33:41.725
- Can I help you?
- Good evening, Miss Peters.

33:41.727 --> 33:43.927
It appears your neighbors have
been hearing unusual noises

33:43.929 --> 33:46.795
coming from your home.

33:46.797 --> 33:49.799
- Unusual noises?
- Screaming.

33:49.801 --> 33:52.338
Young women screaming
at night.

33:54.907 --> 33:57.407
Oh, God.

33:57.409 --> 34:01.578
Oh, God, this is embarrassing.
I, um...

34:01.580 --> 34:04.281
I've recently changed
my medications,

34:04.283 --> 34:06.615
and you see, I've, um...

34:06.617 --> 34:10.319
I'm still getting adjusted.

34:10.321 --> 34:12.621
- I apologize for that.
- No, no, it's okay.

34:12.623 --> 34:15.424
No need to apologize.

34:15.426 --> 34:17.426
Loneliness can make us
do strange things.

34:17.428 --> 34:19.795
[CHUCKLES]
Well, I can guarantee

34:19.797 --> 34:21.630
I will do my best
to make sure these...

34:21.632 --> 34:24.734
[CHUCKLES]
unusual noises end.

34:24.735 --> 34:27.404
Thank you so much stopping by,
Detective Siegel.

34:27.406 --> 34:29.538
It's so thoughtful of you.
Goodbye.

34:29.540 --> 34:32.741
Do you mind if I just
take a look at that leak?

34:32.743 --> 34:34.877
- I'm sorry?
- This leak here.

34:34.879 --> 34:37.480
How long has this been
going on for?

34:37.482 --> 34:40.817
Um, I don't know.

34:40.819 --> 34:42.219
When was the last time
any maintenance

34:42.221 --> 34:44.654
was done on the house?

34:44.656 --> 34:46.922
Oh, I don't know.
My grandparents were the ones

34:46.924 --> 34:49.625
taking care of the maintenance.

34:49.627 --> 34:52.362
You'll have to excuse me.
I'm just...

34:52.364 --> 34:54.330
I'm still in mourning.

34:54.331 --> 34:56.266
My condolences again,
Miss Peters.

34:56.268 --> 34:59.672
It's terrible how they passed
together and so suddenly.

35:01.239 --> 35:03.640
- [DISTANT THUMP]
- Oh!

35:03.642 --> 35:05.241
Don't worry about that.
I've got it. I...

35:05.243 --> 35:06.211
I'll get it.

35:13.451 --> 35:14.884
[LAUGHS]

35:14.886 --> 35:16.620
I remember these two.

35:16.622 --> 35:19.457
You girls were inseparable.

35:22.694 --> 35:24.529
Whatever happened to them?

35:27.933 --> 35:31.301
- Well, I don't know.
- You don't keep in touch?

35:31.303 --> 35:34.270
- No.
- Really? Why not?

35:34.272 --> 35:38.641
My grandparents believed them
to be a poor influence on me.

35:38.643 --> 35:40.846
Yes, of course.

35:42.446 --> 35:43.980
They were on a TV show
not too long ago.

35:43.982 --> 35:46.283
Did you see it?

35:46.285 --> 35:50.386
No. I didn't grow up
with television.

35:50.388 --> 35:51.554
It's odd though,
don't you think?

35:51.556 --> 35:53.022
After all this time,

35:53.024 --> 35:58.295
not a single phone call
or an email.

35:58.297 --> 36:01.031
No, I don't own a computer.

36:01.033 --> 36:04.933
Right.
Probably for the best.

36:04.935 --> 36:07.770
Those girls...

36:07.772 --> 36:10.873
they're no good,
Miss Peters.

36:10.875 --> 36:13.278
They're dangerous,
let me tell you that.

36:19.685 --> 36:20.686
[DAPHNE CHUCKLES]

36:22.788 --> 36:24.657
They're not dangerous.

36:26.692 --> 36:28.460
They're geniuses.

36:32.730 --> 36:37.701
Even my grandparents didn't
understand poetry like they do.

36:37.703 --> 36:39.835
They're brilliant.

36:39.837 --> 36:42.004
- Hmm. I understand.
- No.

36:42.006 --> 36:44.841
- No, you don't know them.
- Miss Peters...

36:44.843 --> 36:46.909
You don't know them
like I know them!

36:46.911 --> 36:48.777
- I'm not trying to upset you.
- No! No!

36:48.779 --> 36:50.112
The world never deserved them.

36:50.114 --> 36:51.948
The outside world
always rejected them!

36:51.950 --> 36:53.583
Rejected?

36:53.585 --> 36:56.652
Now you're going to see
what it's like...

36:56.654 --> 36:58.591
to live without them.

37:00.991 --> 37:02.861
Where are they?

37:05.797 --> 37:07.096
Where are they?

37:07.098 --> 37:10.100
I don't... No!

37:10.102 --> 37:13.569
What?
[GIGGLES]

37:13.571 --> 37:16.373
How'd you know
they went missing?

37:16.375 --> 37:18.942
Um...
[GIGGLES]

37:18.944 --> 37:22.478
Their disappearance isn't
national news, Miss Peters,

37:22.480 --> 37:24.047
so you couldn't have
read about it.

37:24.049 --> 37:26.049
You don't have a TV,
you don't have a computer,

37:26.051 --> 37:28.551
you never leave the house.

37:28.553 --> 37:32.821
You just told me that they
haven't contacted you in years,

37:32.823 --> 37:35.125
so how would you have known
that they went missing?

37:35.127 --> 37:36.462
[DISTANT THUMPS]

37:40.031 --> 37:42.531
- Miss Peters?
- [THUMPING CONTINUES]

37:42.533 --> 37:46.136
Officer, may I see
your search warrant, please?

37:46.138 --> 37:49.772
Because if you don't have one,
I suggest you leave.

37:49.774 --> 37:53.009
Right now.

37:53.011 --> 37:54.911
Unless you want me to call
the police station

37:54.913 --> 37:56.513
and tell them you've
spent your afternoon

37:56.515 --> 38:00.549
searching the home
of the town lunatic!

38:00.551 --> 38:06.188
You're close to retirement,
aren't you, Detective Siegel?

38:06.190 --> 38:10.029
If I were you, I'd wanna retire
with a little dignity.

38:18.469 --> 38:22.705
If I get any more complaints,
Miss Peters,

38:22.707 --> 38:25.141
I'm gonna have to come back
with a warrant.

38:25.143 --> 38:27.109
But you won't mind.

38:27.111 --> 38:30.548
It's not like you're hiding
two fugitives in your attic.

38:33.084 --> 38:35.652
[CHUCKLES]

38:35.654 --> 38:38.455
Par... Pardon me?

38:38.457 --> 38:41.190
That's right.
They're not just missing.

38:41.192 --> 38:42.891
They're wanted, Miss Peters.

38:42.893 --> 38:45.661
But I understand
your need to protect them.

38:45.663 --> 38:49.165
But in the end...

38:49.167 --> 38:51.804
who's gonna protect you
from them?

38:59.678 --> 39:00.980
Take care.

39:08.553 --> 39:14.093
<i>♪♪ [EERIE]</i>

39:17.928 --> 39:19.895
[DOOR SLAMS]

39:19.897 --> 39:24.102
[HAMMERING]

39:28.038 --> 39:32.511
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

39:37.114 --> 39:40.585
[TOY TRAIN WHISTLING]

39:53.899 --> 39:57.136
[TOY TRAIN WHISTLING]

40:54.091 --> 40:56.728
Now no one can come in.

40:58.830 --> 41:01.830
I will always keep you safe.

41:01.832 --> 41:03.799
I promise.

41:03.801 --> 41:05.837
Now, please, sit.

41:07.839 --> 41:10.976
Oh, Tilda,
go wash your hands first.

41:18.015 --> 41:19.884
[SIGHS]
Doctor.

41:22.087 --> 41:24.123
Doctor, I know
what you're here for.

41:27.892 --> 41:30.596
And I've been dying to play.

41:32.330 --> 41:34.163
Into our rotting
mansion's halls,

41:34.165 --> 41:36.732
look for signs along the way.

41:36.734 --> 41:39.969
You'll waltz about
with my dolls,

41:39.971 --> 41:42.971
and let the mirror
end your days.

41:42.973 --> 41:45.741
But caution, dear Doctor,

41:45.743 --> 41:48.277
for you're not
too far from hell.

41:48.279 --> 41:52.781
And the grave will open wide
when you shatter time's spell!

41:52.783 --> 41:54.850
- Time's spell?
- But, but...

41:54.852 --> 41:58.020
if you finish the game
before me, I'll let you go,

41:58.022 --> 41:59.888
and I'll take the blame.

41:59.890 --> 42:02.725
The blame for what?
What are you talking about?

42:02.727 --> 42:05.428
The grave will open wide!

42:05.430 --> 42:07.163
What? Whose grave?

42:07.165 --> 42:10.132
[LAUGHING]
Our rotting mansion's halls!

42:10.134 --> 42:12.902
- Where's Tilda?
- Oh, Doctor!

42:12.904 --> 42:14.069
Dear Doctor, it's too late.

42:14.071 --> 42:16.808
What did you do?
Tilda!

42:18.843 --> 42:20.346
It's too late.

42:22.080 --> 42:23.980
PETULA: [GASPS]
Oh, my God, Tilda.

42:23.982 --> 42:26.214
The grave will open wide
when you shatter time's spell.

42:26.216 --> 42:27.917
- What?
- Just listen to the riddle,

42:27.919 --> 42:29.217
and you'll find the clues
to the safe, okay?

42:29.219 --> 42:32.120
- Just go.
- Daughter, where are you?

42:32.122 --> 42:34.257
- Just go. Go find the safe.
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

42:34.259 --> 42:35.824
Go. We're running out of time.
Just go.

42:35.826 --> 42:37.859
Darling!

42:37.861 --> 42:41.263
Stop bothering
the poor doctor.

42:41.265 --> 42:43.031
Go on, Doctor.

42:43.033 --> 42:45.370
Go waltz about with my dolls.

42:56.080 --> 42:58.017
DAPHNE: Go waltz about
with my dolls.

42:59.250 --> 43:01.654
Go waltz about with my dolls.

43:09.060 --> 43:11.363
<i>♪♪ [TENSE]</i>

43:21.739 --> 43:24.040
[GRUNTS]

43:24.042 --> 43:25.908
Our rotting mansion's halls.

43:25.910 --> 43:27.046
Rotting mansion's halls.

43:31.515 --> 43:33.851
Rotting mansion's halls,
rotting mansion's halls.

43:35.352 --> 43:36.853
Rotting mansion...

43:36.855 --> 43:39.121
[SIGHS]
Come on.

43:39.123 --> 43:42.093
Fuck.
[PANTING]

43:45.129 --> 43:46.962
DAPHNE: <i>Into our rotting
mansion's halls,</i>

43:46.964 --> 43:48.466
<i>look for signs along the way.</i>

44:00.978 --> 44:02.781
Look for signs along the way.

44:04.248 --> 44:06.549
DAPHNE: <i>And let the mirror
end your days.</i>

44:06.551 --> 44:10.255
Let the mirror end your day.
Let the mirror end your day.

44:23.000 --> 44:25.134
"Shatter time's spell."

44:25.136 --> 44:28.103
Shatter time's spell.
What does that mean?

44:28.105 --> 44:30.138
Come on, how do you
shatter time's spell?

44:30.140 --> 44:31.276
[SIGHS]

45:04.341 --> 45:06.144
[SIGHS]

45:33.471 --> 45:36.108
Petula is still
trying to escape.

45:37.341 --> 45:39.641
Daphne will get her.

45:39.643 --> 45:41.446
Daphne always gets her.

45:43.013 --> 45:45.448
I got it.
I got it. I found it.

45:45.450 --> 45:47.382
- What?
- The safe. I found the safe.

45:47.384 --> 45:50.518
No, it's okay.
She agreed to it.

45:50.520 --> 45:53.288
- Agreed to what?
- To letting us go.

45:53.290 --> 45:55.156
We found the safe.
We can keep the money.

45:55.158 --> 45:58.094
We can keep
all of her inheritance.

45:58.096 --> 45:59.929
Come on.
Then we can commit her.

45:59.931 --> 46:01.496
- But how?
- What do you mean, how?

46:01.498 --> 46:03.199
We can pay Coco back.

46:03.201 --> 46:06.134
We can move out of that
shitty crack cave we live in.

46:06.136 --> 46:09.304
Come on, this is a new,
fresh fuckin' start, Tilda.

46:09.306 --> 46:11.343
Come on, get your shit.

46:12.676 --> 46:15.881
We are getting out of here
tonight.

46:18.415 --> 46:19.484
Come on.

46:22.152 --> 46:23.351
Shit.

46:23.353 --> 46:24.489
Watch yourself.

46:26.424 --> 46:27.893
Petula, hold up!

46:33.665 --> 46:34.933
Slow down!

46:46.576 --> 46:48.710
PETULA: Hey!

46:48.712 --> 46:50.679
Hey, hey!

46:50.681 --> 46:52.047
Stop!

46:52.049 --> 46:54.449
Are you fucking kidding me?

46:54.451 --> 46:56.421
Fucking asshole!

47:00.725 --> 47:02.158
- No.
- [CAR PASSES]

47:02.160 --> 47:03.591
Fuck!

47:03.593 --> 47:06.261
You wanna fucking help me?
Not just sit there?

47:06.263 --> 47:08.563
What do you want me to do?
What am I supposed to do?

47:08.565 --> 47:10.598
Help me! Help me flag down
one of the fucking cars!

47:10.600 --> 47:13.736
It's not gonna make a difference
if I stand up or not.

47:13.738 --> 47:17.073
- I'm fucking tired!
- I'm fucking tired, Tilda!

47:17.075 --> 47:19.542
- Come on!
- Just shut the fuck up.

47:19.544 --> 47:22.277
- Are you serious right now?
- Nobody's fucking out here.

47:22.279 --> 47:24.181
Just get off your
fucking ass and help...

47:26.616 --> 47:27.919
[TIRES SCREECH]

47:33.690 --> 47:37.161
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

47:43.634 --> 47:46.368
DAPHNE: Tsk, tsk, tsk, tsk.

47:46.370 --> 47:47.670
Where's Tilda?

47:47.672 --> 47:50.373
Oh, she's in bed.

47:50.375 --> 47:52.375
Would you like to see her?

47:52.377 --> 47:55.210
You said if we found the safe,
then you'd let us go.

47:55.212 --> 47:58.350
I said <i>you</i> could go.

48:00.051 --> 48:02.051
And I said you had to finish
the game first,

48:02.053 --> 48:03.989
and you haven't.

48:05.256 --> 48:08.324
- [TILDA SOBS]
- She's awake.

48:08.326 --> 48:10.661
Would you like me
to take you to her?

48:14.131 --> 48:16.699
[DAPHNE HUMMING
"ROW, ROW, ROW YOUR BOAT"]

48:16.701 --> 48:17.732
No.

48:17.734 --> 48:20.435
[HUMMING CONTINUES]

48:20.437 --> 48:23.274
[PETULA PANTING]

48:25.442 --> 48:28.476
- There we are.
- [PETULA SOBS]

48:28.478 --> 48:29.647
PETULA: Tilda?

48:32.350 --> 48:33.752
DAPHNE: Daughter.

48:37.120 --> 48:39.056
Hello, dearest.

48:40.625 --> 48:43.259
Say hello, darling.

48:43.261 --> 48:46.031
Darling girl, don't be rude.

48:47.364 --> 48:50.565
Oh, this night
is so exhilarating.

48:50.567 --> 48:53.569
You know, it reminds me...

48:53.571 --> 48:56.705
of the night...

48:56.707 --> 48:59.243
that I poisoned my grandparents.

49:02.245 --> 49:05.614
They wanted
to get me a caretaker.

49:05.616 --> 49:08.384
Like I was some kind
of crazy person.

49:08.386 --> 49:10.422
[LAUGHS]

49:13.723 --> 49:16.391
TILDA: No, Mother.
Mother, please don't.

49:16.393 --> 49:19.495
Mother, please, please don't.
Mother, please!

49:19.497 --> 49:22.297
You, keep your eyes open.

49:22.299 --> 49:26.768
- I haven't taken those yet.
- [TILDA CRYING]

49:26.770 --> 49:28.837
Daphne, no.
[SOBS]

49:28.839 --> 49:33.109
[TILDA SCREAMING]

49:33.111 --> 49:35.547
[SCREAMING CONTINUES]

49:43.821 --> 49:46.558
[WAILS]

49:56.334 --> 49:58.766
OFFICER: Take that away, Grover.

49:58.768 --> 50:01.303
- Harrison.
- What you got, Mort?

50:01.305 --> 50:03.739
Guy says he's seen
the missing girls.

50:03.741 --> 50:07.877
- Oh, yeah?
- Outside the train station.

50:07.879 --> 50:11.379
They look mermaids on crack.

50:11.381 --> 50:13.748
You seen these two girls?
You positive?

50:13.750 --> 50:18.154
Yeah. Them's the mermaids.

50:18.156 --> 50:20.255
Now, where's my reward?

50:20.257 --> 50:22.757
MORT: You also see flying cats,
you quack.

50:22.759 --> 50:24.859
How long ago?

50:24.861 --> 50:27.163
MORT: Come on.

50:27.165 --> 50:28.364
- You're not a bum?
- No.

50:28.366 --> 50:29.568
Get outta here.
Get him outta here.

50:33.937 --> 50:36.304
Hello, Tilda.

50:36.306 --> 50:38.207
Petula.

50:38.209 --> 50:40.875
I've come to tell you
that the game is over.

50:40.877 --> 50:43.147
So you can go now.

50:45.183 --> 50:46.318
It's been fun.

50:49.754 --> 50:52.254
Oh.

50:52.256 --> 50:55.560
Before I go, a goodbye gift.

50:59.330 --> 51:01.533
Drug dealers, huh?

51:04.801 --> 51:08.439
You know, maybe they won't
recognize you with the scars.

51:10.774 --> 51:13.708
Well, you wanted
to leave so badly,

51:13.710 --> 51:16.480
so why don't you just leave?

51:19.382 --> 51:21.685
Clear this room immediately!

51:24.254 --> 51:28.223
There's lots to be done
before the baby comes.

51:28.225 --> 51:29.958
These walls need to be
repainted and...

51:29.960 --> 51:32.464
TILDA: What the fuck
are you talking about, Daphne?

51:35.600 --> 51:36.966
I'm sorry?

51:36.968 --> 51:40.636
You're not pregnant,
you psycho bitch.

51:40.638 --> 51:42.770
You can't be.

51:42.772 --> 51:43.906
You're insane.

51:43.908 --> 51:45.306
You know that, right?

51:45.308 --> 51:47.009
I mean, you must know that.

51:47.011 --> 51:48.611
Please keep your voice down.

51:48.613 --> 51:50.779
The stress isn't good
for the baby.

51:50.781 --> 51:52.013
TILDA: What baby?

51:52.015 --> 51:53.748
There's no baby.
You're barren.

51:53.750 --> 51:56.551
I feel it.

51:56.553 --> 51:59.855
I feel it kick in the night.

51:59.857 --> 52:01.422
In the night, it kicks and...

52:01.424 --> 52:03.792
Shut the fuck up, Daphne.

52:03.794 --> 52:05.460
What kind of mother
do you think you'd be?

52:05.462 --> 52:08.730
- It kicks in the night.
- Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

52:08.732 --> 52:10.899
Oh, my God,
are you listening to yourself?

52:10.901 --> 52:14.370
He comes in the night,
and he's coming tonight.

52:14.372 --> 52:16.705
